      "text": "Reducing Generator Interconnect Procedures (GIP) Timeline\n\nSkip to main content Skip to footer\n\nEngage MISO Dashboard Reducing Generator Interconnect Procedures (GIP) Timeline\n\nFollow\n\n# MISO Dashboard\n\n#### Last Modified - 03/22/2023\n\n## Reducing Generator Interconnect Procedures (GIP) Timeline IPWG003\n\nLegend\n\n#### Status\n\nActive - Issue is progressing through the Stakeholder Process.\n\nCompleted - Issue is resolved or implemented.\n\nClosed - Work on issue is discontinued.\n\nOn Hold - Work on issue is suspended.\n\nInactive - An issue for future consideration.\n\nPending - Issue is not ready to be assigned a status; will be updated in the future.\n\n#### Phase\n\nE\n\nExplore - Gauge interest, determine feasibility and set scope of work (previous phases of Frame and Evaluate)\n\nD\n\nDesign - Examine and compare issue solutions and design, engage stakeholder process (previous phase of Concept Design)\n\nB\n\nBuild - Software functional specification; vendor software design; hardware procurement; software development, validation & testing; update business practice manuals; operator and stakeholder training\n\nI\n\nImplement - Operational transitional phase, implement production system\n\nFERC\n\nFERC - Project to be filed or is filed with FERC; awaiting response\n\nBPM\n\nBPM - Development of new or amended Business Practice Manual (BPM) language required\n\nNone - There is no phase\n\n#### Indicator\n\nferc-border\n\nFERC - Phase work continues while awaiting FERC Order.\n\nbpm-border\n\nBPM - Phase work continues while and Business Practice Manual (BPM) language under development.\n\nferc-with-bpm-border\n\nFERC and BPM Border - Phase work and BPM language under development while awaiting FERC Order.\n\nno-border\n\nNo border -\n\n#### Category\n\nMarket Redefinition -\n\nTransmission Evolution -\n\nOperations of the Future -\n\nSystem Enhancement -\n\nResource Availability and Need -\n\nDistributed Energy Resources -\n\nAttributes -\n\nE\n\nE\n\nE\n\nE\n\nE\n\nE\n\nE\n\nB\n\nI\n\nI\n\nBPM\n\nBPM\n\n| 2019 | 2020 | 2021 | 2022 | 2023 |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Q1 | Q2 | Q3 | Q4 | Q1 | Q2 | Q3 | Q4 | Q1 | Q2 | Q3 | Q4 | Q1 | Q2 | Q3 | Q4 | Q1 | Q2 | Q3 | Q4 |\n\n#### Overview\n\n##### Phase\n\nBPM\n\n##### Entities\n\nActive: Planning Advisory Committee (PAC)\n\n##### Next Update\n\n##### Status\n\nCompleted\n\n##### MISO Initiatives\n\n#### Quick Link\n\n#### Related Pages\n\nCurrently there is an alignment gap between the GIP timeline and the MTEP process. MTEP projects are approved annually whereas the GIP takes 505 days. To better coordinate the two planning processes it will be necessary to reduce the GIP timeline to align better with the annual MTEP process.\n\nThis is a sub issue to the umbrella Integrated Roadmap Issue IR072 (Queue Enhancements).\n\n### Updates\n\n#### 03/08/2023\n\nPAC liaison report included an update on this issue. After opening a window for feedback on proposed BPM-015 language, MISO received two responses supporting the updates. One piece of feedback was out of scope and will be addressed with the submitter as the BPM language simply memorializes approved tariff language. For now, no changes to the BPM updates will be made.\n\n#### 01/25/2023\n\nMISO presentation to PAC summarizing discussion from October IPWG / proposed changes to BPM-015 for which no feedback was received. PAC Sectors were invited to submit final feedback by February 8.\n\n#### 10/10/2022\n\nMISO presentation to IPWG summarizing BPM-015 changes to accommodate the accepted tariff filing on GIP timeline reduction. Feedback requested by October 28, 2022.\n\n#### 09/22/2021\n\nFinal presentation given to PAC including a summary of the final round of stakeholder feedback and final proposal. Tariff revisions to be filed in Q4 2021.\n\n#### 08/11/2021\n\nPAC review of extensive procedural revisions (Attachment X) developed with IPWG. The proposal now allows for a path towards a 1 calendar year GIP study timeline; updates GI process to align with current practices; provides enhanced flexibility in the study process; and ensures a future with improved MISO MTEP alignment. Feedback requested by September 1.\n\nShow\n\nEntries\n\nShowing 1-5 of 15\n\n123\n\n### Issue Materials\n\n#### Documents/Whitepapers\n\n20230125 PAC Item 05a GIP Timeline Reduction Presentation.pdf\n\n05/16/2025\n\nFollow\n\n20230308 PAC Item 03 Liaison Report.pdf\n\n05/16/2025\n\nFollow\n\n20230125 PAC Item 05a GIP Timeline Reduction BPM Edits.docx\n\n05/16/2025\n\nFollow\n\n#### FERC Filings and Orders\n\nThere are currently no FERC Filings and Orders that match this criteria.",
